programme.title: Auction Hunters: Knuckle Dust
programme.desc: 1870s French Jarre Dolne Knuckle Duster revolver-knife-brass knuckle combo, a rare original George Rodrigue "Blue Dog" screenprint and a 1980 autographed Raging Bull movie poster.

programme.title: Auction Hunters: Quadzilla Attacks!
programme.desc: Extreme Quadzilla ATV, the fastest 4 wheeler ever; a 1910s Remington Derringer and an 1880s Palm Squeezer pistol; revolutionary 1800s Western Electric telephone with a crank dial.

programme.title: Auction Hunters: The Smoking Ton
programme.desc: WW2 Stuart M3 tank barrel and heavy duty tank treads; rare, collectors' 1890 silver inlayed humidor; high-end industrial meat slicer in the ultimate restaurant unit.

programme.title: Auction Hunters: Top Gun Ton
programme.desc: Scale RC Viper FanJet aircraft with a potent jet engine; 1920s Gundlach Korona large format field camera used for photography expeditions. Ton pilots a plane, but crashes and burns.

programme.title: Auction Hunters: Hot Wheels
programme.desc: '70s sand rail dune racer with rally hemi heads; 1965 replica Mustang pool table; off-road racing gear.

programme.title: Auction Hunters: Choo-Choo, Cha-Ching!
programme.desc: Ton and Allen get a surprise second chance after nearly getting shut out in the small town of Palmer. They uncover a motorized railroad maintenance car from the 1960's and a pre-WWI Japanese semi-automatic pistol.

programme.title: Auction Hunters: Everything's Bigger in Texas
programme.desc: Winchester 1886 rifle invented to kill buffalo; collection of 1950s electric Slot Cars.

programme.title: Auction Hunters: Ton's Hot Commodity
programme.desc: Allen is late to the auction, leaving Ton to battle a feisty female auction buyer on his own! The guys find a fully functional flamethrower and a rare hand-carved bow and arrow set from South America!

programme.title: Auction Hunters: Strat'ed for Cash
programme.desc: On a limited budget in the historic L.A. neighborhood of West Adams, Allen and Ton still win three lockers and find a Maui Blue Fender Stratocaster and a 1930s Schwinn bike.

programme.title: Auction Hunters: Sidecar Surprise
programme.desc: An unassuming mom in an oversized sweater tries to pull the wool over Ton & Allen's eyes at a storage auction in Arlington, VA. The guys uncover a black powder cannon designed in the 15th century & a Russian military motorcycle!

programme.title: Auction Hunters: Gangster Whiskey
programme.desc: Allen and Ton trek to an auction in Moreno Valley, CA, where two locker wins yield a vintage jukebox, a valuable baseball card and a Prohibition-era moonshine still.

programme.title: Auction Hunters: The Wild West
programme.desc: Allen and Ton explain their strategies at a storage auction in San Bernardino, win two units, then have a Pepperbox gun and vintage Lionel train set appraised by experts.

programme.title: Auction Hunters: Money Makin' Monster Machines
programme.desc: The Auction Hunters team goes on the attack & ends up on a collision course with a hardened veteran auction buyer. They uncover a collection of speedy off-road vehicles and some hardcore heavy metal from the turn-of the-century!

programme.title: Auction Hunters: Allen's Got Balls
programme.desc: After returning to LA, Ton & Allen head deep into hostile auction hunter territory and butt heads with a familiar old foe! They discover a driving range golf ball picker vehicle and one of the most accurate rifles ever made!

programme.title: Auction Hunters: Mr. Haff Goes to Washington
programme.desc: Ton and Allen invade the Nation's capital, but meet strong resistance from local bidders. The guys uncover a Civil War era black powder revolver and a stash of South African gold coins!

programme.title: Auction Hunters: Beantown Bidders
programme.desc: 1800s blackpowder whaling harpoon; 1940s Schwinn Town & Country tandem bicycle; a vintage American flag collection that could be worth thousands.

programme.title: Auction Hunters: The Big Score
programme.desc: At a climate-controlled storage facility in downtown L.A., Allen and Ton's locker wins score them an antique cash register and a German H&K pistol prized by collectors.

programme.title: Auction Hunters: Gold 'n' Gloves
programme.desc: The Auction Hunters team goes toe-to-toe with Ton's evil twin! They find a medieval catapult designed for storming castles and Ton uncovers a hidden collection of gold bars worth thousands of dollars!

programme.title: Auction Hunters: Friends in Hawaii Places
programme.desc: Allen &Ton enlist an assistant, Carolyn, and Allen's Hawaiian buddy, Junior, to help them battle local buyers. The guys find a WWII-era motor scooter and a stash of antique Polynesian tattoo tools that get used on Ton!

programme.title: Auction Hunters: The Dallas Mavericks
programme.desc: Military-grade Tomahawk cruise missile jet engine; century-old handcrafted wild west cowboy saddle; 1960s high roller's gold money.

programme.title: It's Christmas Carol!
programme.desc: Inspired by the Charles Dickens classic A Christmas Carol, It’s Christmas Carol! tells the story of a driven, heartless, publishing executive, Carol Huffman, who on Christmas Eve is visited by the ghost of her former boss, Eve.

programme.title: K9 Christmas: Scoot & Kassie's Christmas Adventure
programme.desc: Kassie rescues Scoot, a former K-9 police dog, who becomes her best friend. But when two men turn up to work at the bank that Kassie's dad (Luke Perry) manages she finds out they are crooks with plans to get their hands on all the money and ruin Christmas

programme.title: One Starry Christmas
programme.desc: Aspiring astronomy professor and Christmas enthusiast Holly is crushed when her longtime boyfriend Adam schedules a business trip and leaves her alone over the holidays.

programme.title: A Christmoose Story
programme.desc: A large moose crashes through the roof of young Max's garage! A moose who talks! A moose who claims to work for Santa!

programme.title: Best Christmas Party Ever
programme.desc: Jennie Stanton (Torrey DeVitto) throws the best Christmas parties every year for her company, Petra's Parties.

programme.title: Holiday Wishes
programme.desc: Britney, a rich, spoiled child, and Rachel, an orphan, switch bodies after a visit to the mall with Santa Claus. Each girl wakes up as the other - Britney is in the orphanage, and Rachel is at Britney's family's mansion.

programme.title: Merry Matrimony
programme.desc: An ad exec for a fashion magazine lands her dream assignment to organize the perfect Christmas wedding. Just one thing. The photographer she's been partnered with is her ex-boyfriend.

programme.title: Holiday in Your Heart
programme.desc: Fourteen-year-old LeAnn Rimes wants nothing more than to sing at the Grand Ole Opry. She is invited to sing at a Christmas concert on Nashville's famous stage, but upon her arrival, she is faced with a difficult decision.

programme.title: Chasing Christmas
programme.desc: A bitter and burned-out Ghost of Christmas Past decides to go AWOL.

programme.title: Sarah's House: Master Bedroom
programme.desc: Sarah Richardson introduces romance to this large, builder beige master bedroom. Sarah kicks it all off with botanical inspired fabrics and prints, fresh crisp paint colours and wallpaper on a feature wall. A vintage desk...

programme.title: Sarah's House: Master Ensuite
programme.desc: The oversized master ensuite in this new build suburban house is proof that you can have too much of a good thing...

programme.title: Sarah's House: Rec Room
programme.desc: An all purpose room the entire family can enjoy. Sarah Richardson invested a serious amount of her upgrade on a basement walkout to the backyard, and ups and ante by combining a series of small boxy rooms into one multi-purpose destination...

programme.title: Sarah's House: Curb Appeal, Finale
programme.desc: Most new build homes come with little more than a patch of grass and struggling sapling. Sarah Richardson revises the front-scape of the custom suburban home with plantings and accessories that convey a “been there all along” appeal...

programme.title: Sarah's Rental Cottage: Living Room, Exterior
programme.desc: Sarah and her husband Alexander buy a charming 1950’s cottage on an island to renovate as a rental. Her husband initially tentative, Sarah paints the wood-paneled living room white and the floors a showstopper green.

programme.title: Sarah's Rental Cottage: Kitchen, Solar
programme.desc: The dark cottage kitchen gets the heave-ho in favor of something brighter, more modern, and practical for renters.

programme.title: Sarah's Rental Cottage: Master Bedroom, Siding
programme.desc: This master bedroom has great bones, with a high vaulted ceiling and lots of windows. Sarah and Tommy use the power of paint to lighten the space and repurpose some of the built-in furniture.

programme.title: Sarah's Rental Cottage: Bathroom, Sunset Deck
programme.desc: The cottage’s single bathroom has seen better days. Sarah replaces dated finishes and fixtures with stylish, hardwearing solutions. The window is enlarged and Alexander clears trees to bring in more light.

programme.title: Sarah's Rental Cottage: Guest Room, Deck
programme.desc: Sarah and Alexander clear out a packed storage room and turn it into an extra bedroom, boosting the number of guests this rental cottage can accommodate.

programme.title: Sarah's Rental Cottage: Bunkroom, Screen Porch
programme.desc: It’s the perfect kids’ space, with plenty of bunk beds and waterside location. Sarah votes to keep the nautical theme buy using the color blue as jumping off point, with more space saving fun touches like hanging baskets.

programme.desc: We catch up with the girls of 16 And Pregnant to find where they are now.

programme.desc: Once her days were filled with college applications and racing quad bikes with friends, but after getting pregnant, Katie has to completely rearrange her priorities.

programme.title: 16 & Pregnant: Lindsey
programme.desc: When Lindsey unexpectedly gets pregnant, she struggles to find a stable living situation with her inconsistent boyfriend, and to follow through with her dreams.

programme.title: 16 & Pregnant: Alex
programme.desc: Alex finding out she's pregnant at 16 puts everything on hold. Her boyfriend Matt is also growing increasingly unreliable, and Alex considers whether adoption might be the best choice.

programme.title: NEW EPISODES CSI: NY: Redemption
programme.desc: A death row inmate's final request brings Hawkes to a Pennsylvania prison and face-to-face with a personal secret just as a prison riot erupts.

programme.title: NEW EPISODES CSI: NY: Uncertainty Rules
programme.desc: When four victims are found dead in a hotel room and the main suspect turns up wielding an ax, the CSIs try to piece together the details.

programme.title: NEW EPISODES CSI: NY: Help
programme.desc: Young brides-to-be fight over a killer dress at the biggest wedding gown sale of the year and one of the shoppers winds up dead.

programme.title: NEW EPISODES CSI: NY: Page Turner
programme.desc: A free street concert quickly turns into a crime scene, the victim, in this case, has been mysteriously plagued with radiation.

programme.title: NEW EPISODES CSI: New York: My Name Is Mac Taylor
programme.desc: When two men who share the same name as detective Mac Taylor are killed, detective Taylor rounds up all the other Mac Taylors in New York and tries to figure out who will be the next victim.

programme.title: NEW EPISODES CSI: New York: Pay Up
programme.desc: A group of violent kidnappers capture Robert Dunbrook's son just before he is scheduled to testify to a grand jury against his father, and the CSI team is rocked by a tragedy.

programme.title: NEW EPISODES CSI: New York: Manhattanhenge
programme.desc: Mac and the team lose the Compass Killer at the World's Fair site, and they soon discover through the use of astronomy and sunrises that it's only a matter of time before he targets the next victim.

programme.title: NEW EPISODES CSI: New York: Blacklist (Featuring Gravedigger)
programme.desc: The case of a cyber killer, who appears to be targeting medical health-care workers, turns personal when the suspect invokes the name of Mac's father who had died nearly two decades earlier.

programme.title: NEW EPISODES CSI: New York: One Wedding and a Funeral
programme.desc: Mac, Danny and Hawkes investigates a groom murdered on his wedding day, found stuffed and wrapped like a wedding present. Stella and Lindsay investigate when a jigsaw covered in blood is left on Stella's car.

programme.title: NEW EPISODES CSI: New York: Rest in Peace Marina Garito
programme.desc: Sid rules the death of a woman whose twin brother disappeared 15 years ago a suicide, but Stella is convinced that he is wrong and sets out to prove it.

programme.title: NEW EPISODES CSI: New York: Redemption
programme.desc: Dr. Hawkes is trapped in a cell block during a security breach orchestrated by a familiar face from CSI's past, and the only person who can help him get to safety is the death row inmate who murdered his sister.

programme.title: NEW EPISODES CSI: New York: Veritas
programme.desc: Immediately following the previous season finale, the team is investigating the death of a woman named Lauren Salinas who is linked to the bank robbery. She turns out to be a friend of Flack's sister Samantha.

programme.title: NEW EPISODES CSI: New York: Child's Play
programme.desc: Flack and Stella investigate a man killed by an exploding cigar. Danny and his neighbor Ruben stumble on a bodega robbery and the boy is killed by a stray bullet. Danny is filled with guilt because he was supposed to be responsible for the child.

programme.title: NEW EPISODES CSI: New York: Criminal Justice
programme.desc: A murder trial is delayed and the suspect is released on bail after Stella discovers that the district attorney in the case tampered with the crime scene for personal gain.

programme.title: NEW EPISODES CSI: New York: Turbulence
programme.desc: When an Air Marshal turns up dead on a flight on which Mac is a passenger, the victim it turns out, isn't a Marshal at all. The real Marshal was killed earlier and his ID stolen.

programme.title: NEW EPISODES CSI: New York: Dead Inside
programme.desc: A man is found dead in a basement, but the house where the death occurred is found miles away on a barge in the East River. Meanwhile, Flack discovers that his sister lost her job and has a drinking problem.

programme.title: NEW EPISODES CSI: Miami: From The Grave
programme.desc: Horatio and the CSI team face off with Miami’s notorious and deadly Mala Noche gang after a funeral becomes the scene of a murder.

programme.title: NEW EPISODES CSI: Miami: Open Water
programme.desc: While investigating the disappearance of a cruise ship passenger, the team discovers that a murder has also taken place on the ship.

programme.title: NEW EPISODES CSI: Miami: Dead Air
programme.desc: A cell phone call leads the team to investigate a kidnapping that, unless they reach the victim before it’s too late, could soon become a murder.

programme.title: NEW EPISODES CSI: Miami: Inside Out
programme.desc: Horatio and the CSI team exhaustively search for Horatio’s son after he goes missing during a surprising and deadly prison break.

programme.title: NEW EPISODES CSI: Miami: No Man's Land
programme.desc: The robbery of a police truck containing confiscated weapons is connected to a plot to spring Clavo Cruz from prison, and one of the guns stolen in the robbery is used in the shooting of a young boy.

programme.title: NEW EPISODES CSI: Miami: Blood in the Water
programme.desc: When a rich family is trapped on a burning yacht in shark-infested waters, the CSI's must investigate how it happened.

programme.title: NEW EPISODES CSI: Miami: Down To The Wire
programme.desc: A notorious private investigator becomes a central figure in an investigation into a phony 911 call that ends in death, and he uses information he's gathered about Calleigh and Eric to get them thrown off the case.

programme.title: NEW EPISODES CSI: Miami: Burned
programme.desc: While investigating a possible arson case, Horatio discovers that Yelina is back in Miami working as a private investigator. Meanwhile, Wolfe's prior relationship with one of the suspects gets him in hot water with his superiors.

programme.title: NEW EPISODES CSI: Miami: Sunblock
programme.desc: A man is killed during an eclipse. But when a second person is killed in her home, Horatio suspects that he may be dealing with a serial killer who targets his victims only at night.

programme.title: NEW EPISODES CSI: Miami: Skeletons
programme.desc: When Horatio's nemesis, Walter Resden, targets someone from their past, Horatio tries to stop him. Delko's relationship with Natalia is tested when she thinks she may be pregnant.

programme.title: NEW EPISODES CSI: Miami: CSI Trilogy: One of Our Own
programme.desc: Horatio and Delko search Miami to bring down the Mala Noche gang once and for all. The quest to end the crime-spree is jeopardized when Federal agents, led by Agent Glen Cole, raid the CSI lab searching for missing cash evidence, based on an unknown tip.
programme.sub-title: CSI Trilogy: One of Our Own

programme.title: NEW EPISODES CSI: Miami: Kill Switch
programme.desc: While CSI tries to find out who killed a carjacker, Wolfe is forced to become an adversary as he takes a job as a television crime analyst.

programme.title: NEW EPISODES CSI: Miami: Come As You Are
programme.desc: The death of a Marine recruiter ultimately leads Horatio to open an investigation into the death of a soldier in Iraq. The soldier's brother claims responsibility, but Horatio suspects a cover-up.

programme.title: NEW EPISODES CSI: Miami: Dead Air
programme.desc: The CSI team must locate a woman who has been kidnapped and dialed a wrong number on her cell phone. To locate her, the team must first figure out who the kidnapped woman was trying to contact.

programme.title: NEW EPISODES CSI: Miami: Tunnel Vision
programme.desc: The team finds a body in a sinkhole, which turns out to be related to an underground bank robbery. The case also involves an incriminating video of a wealthy businessman's daughter with a drug dealer.

programme.title: Fame Kills: Fallen Starlet
programme.desc: Actress Rebecca Schaeffer, star of the hit sitcom My Sister Sam, is found shot dead on her LA doorstep. Investigators must unlock the secrets of a puzzling crime scene to catch her killer.

programme.title: Fame Kills: Nashville Nightmare
programme.desc: Melissa Haferman is an aspiring country singer on the verge of a recording contract. She goes missing after travelling to Nashville to record a demo and is found strangled with her own rodeo belt.

programme.title: Fame Kills: Fatal Audition
programme.desc: Actress Karin Schlegel heads to a shoot for a print ad…and vanishes. When her body turns up nude on top of an apartment building, the police investigation reveals a psychologically twisted killer.

programme.title: Fame Kills: Hunted In Hollywood

programme.title: Bake With Anna Olson: Marzipan
programme.desc: Marzipan is made simply from ground almonds mixed with sugar to achieve a paste, but it has so many uses in the dessert world. This episode showcases marzipan from its fundamental creation to its many uses.

programme.title: Bake With Anna Olson: Italian Meringue
programme.desc: Italian meringue is made from whipping egg whites and pouring in boiled sugar, giving the meringue strength and structure to be used in many ways. This episode shows the many applications of this fundamental baking principle.

programme.title: Bake With Anna Olson: Icebox Cookies
programme.desc: An icebox cookie must spendtime chilling before it is sliced and baked, and this episode shows a number of traditional (and even international) styles.

programme.title: Bake With Anna Olson: Buttercream
programme.desc: The most popular of frostings, buttercream comes in all flavours, but also in a variety of techniques. This episode demonstrates the basic styles of buttercream frosting, but also the cake style that suit each type best.

programme.title: Bake With Anna Olson: Petit Fours
programme.desc: Part of the French Petit Fours world, little cakes are truly something special. These individual, two-bite cakes are each baked in a particular pan, and have such an interesting story behind them.

programme.title: Bake With Anna Olson: Flat Breads
programme.desc: Flat breads are a common bread style around the world, with each culture having its own style. This episode showcases a number of the most popular or common flatbreads.

programme.title: Bake With Anna Olson: Savoury Pies
programme.desc: This episode showcases the dough recipe that best suits savoury fillings, and adapts common pastry principles to achieve a flaky and tender savoury result.

programme.title: Bake With Anna Olson: Sponge Cakes
programme.desc: A pastry chef MUST master making sponge cakes, since they are the foundation for so many classic desserts. Light and airy, sponge cakes embody that great balance of technique and creativity and this lesson shows how limitless the options are.

programme.title: Bake With Anna Olson: Bagels And Pretzels
programme.desc: Bagels and pretzels can be categorized under the same umbrella, since they share the common technique of being boiled before they are baked. This lesson really comes through as the basics are expanded on, growing into more elaborate styles.

programme.title: Bake With Anna Olson: Batter Cookies
programme.desc: Some cookies are made from a dough that can be scooped, others are sliced and still others baked twice. Batter cookies start with a soft batter that is then shaped, piped or formed before baking, and are a classic part of a pastry chef’s repertoire.

programme.title: Bake With Anna Olson: Bread Pudding
programme.desc: This style of dessert falls into the category of custard, since the bread is baked in an egg- cream mixture to achieve its delicate richness. The principles behind the custard base and the baking technique demonstrate the versatility of this dessert style

programme.title: Bake With Anna Olson: Trifle
programme.desc: There’s nothing trifling about a good trifle! To call a dessert a trifle it must have layers of cake, cream and fruit, and that leaves a lot of room for classic and creativity.

programme.title: Bake With Anna Olson: Cake Cookies
programme.desc: Cake cookies are soft and moist like a cake, but you bake them on a tray like a traditional cookie. This episode demonstrates the cake-like batter and how to achieve the best, fluffiest results – featuring some original as well as old-fashioned variations

programme.title: Bake With Anna Olson: Muffins
programme.desc: Muffins are a staple for mornings and snack breaks, and their small portioning make them an easy treat.

programme.title: Bake With Anna Olson: Waffles
programme.desc: Waffles are definitely a part of a baker’s repertoire and that woven waffles shape is now known the world around. Here we explore North American, Italian & Belgian styles of waffles.

programme.title: Bake With Anna Olson: Fruit Mousse
programme.desc: Fruit mousses are a staple in patisseries, and come in all sorts of colours and shapes. They can be a dessert on their own or part of a grand torte, and there are a number of ways to maximize the fruit flavour and pop of colour.

programme.title: Bake With Anna Olson: Ice Cream
programme.desc: Pastry chefs are responsible for making their own ice cream in restaurants, and our creativity can really shine through.

programme.title: Bake With Anna Olson: Swiss Meringue
programme.desc: We’ve covered French Meringue and Italian Meringue, so it’s natural to include the third and final style here: Swiss. Egg whites and sugar are heated together and then whipped into frothy heaven. It can be used on its own or as part of another dessert.

programme.title: Bake With Anna Olson: Fruit Preserves
programme.desc: These recipes will give you the essentials behind making fruit preserves and also show you some classic uses.
